HEADWORD: Legislation
<hw>Leg`is*la"tion</hw> <pr>(-l⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>l⟦eacute⟧gislation</ets>, L. <ets>legis latio</ets>.
See <er>Legislator</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of legislating; preparation
and enactment of laws; the laws enacted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pythagoras joined <qex>legislation</qex> to his philosophy.</q>
